radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is distended, measures 11 cm, fluid-filled, and with enhancing wall and fat stranding. No focal lung consolidation, no pleural effusion, no pericardial effusion. Liver enhances homogeneously; no biliary duct dilatation. Spleen, pancreas, and kidneys are unremarkable. No lymphadenopathy. Free fluid in the pelvis. Focal wall thickening in small bowel distal ileum.
